{# TITLE: More About Our Services #}<p><b><a name="Hand">Hand Therapy</a></b></p>
<p>The hand therapist will work with each client in setting up an individualized rehab program with an emphasis but not limited to rehab exercises, adaptive splinting/bracing and ergonomic assessment. These techniques would allow each client to regain independence in their everyday tasks as well as vocational activities.</p>
<p><b><a name="Ortho">Orthopedic Rehabilitation for the Pediatric and Adolescent Patient</a></b></p>
<p><b></b>Our staff specializes in the rehabilitation of orthopedic and sports-related injuries.</p>
<p>Experience a personalized treatment plan in our state-of-the-art facility. We understand the needs of the pediatric and adolescent patient and design treatment programs to facilitate a safe and quick return to prior activities. Our highly trained staff also provides patient education and strength programs to help decrease the risk of re-injury.</p>
<p>Common Pediatric &amp; Adolescent conditions treated at Jersey Sports Medicine &amp; Rehab:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Osgood-Schlatter disease</li>
    <li>Chondromalacia</li>
    <li>Tendinitis</li>
    <li>Sprains</li>
    <li>Strains</li>
    <li>Fractures</li>
    <li>Knee injuries</li>
    <li>ACL / PCL injuries</li>
    <li>Meniscal tears</li>
    <li>Shoulder injuries</li>
    <li>Tennis elbow</li>
    <li>Little leaguer&rsquo;s elbow</li>
    <li>Back pain</li>
    <li>Foot / ankle injuries</li>
    <li>Torticollis</li>
</ul>
